briefdescription.para: This file contains all the functions prototypes for the DMA firmware library. How to use this driver? (+) At first, use DMA_DeInit(...) to reset requires DMA channel. (+) Then, use DMA_Init(...) with DMA initialization structure to initialize a DMA channel. For details on the DMA initialization structure, see "DMA_InitTypeDef". (+) Use DMA_ITConfig(...) to enable interrupts that require DMA channel, and you need to implement the corresponding channel service function: DMA_Channelx_IRQHandler. For details on the DMA interrupt type, see DMA interrupts type definition. (+) Finally, use DMA_Cmd(...) to start a DMA channel transfer. (+) Of course, you can use DMA_GetFlagStatus(...) to get the state of the DMA channel at any time, this is helpful in determining whether the DMA channel has completed its transfer. (+) Note: DMA channels can transfer up to 4095 units at a time.
